	<fdd:sustainabilityFactors>
		<fdd:disclosure>Open standard. MXF developed by the Society of Motion Picture and Television Engineers (SMPTE), a member of the American National Standards Institute (ANSI).  JPEG 2000 developed by Joint Technical Committee ISOAEC JTC 1, Information technology, Subcommittee SC 29, in collaboration with ITU-T.</fdd:disclosure>
		<fdd:documentation>MXF: SMPTE 378M-2004, Material Exchange Format (MXF) -- Operational pattern 1A (Single Item, Single Package) (and other specifications); JPEG 2000: ISO/IEC 15444-1:2000. Information technology -- JPEG 2000 image coding system -- Part 1: Core coding system.</fdd:documentation>
		<fdd:adoption>
			<p>MXF OP1a is supported in a number of systems; see <fddLink id="fdd000013">MXF</fddLink>. JPEG 2000 is seeing increasing adoption in 2005 and later; see <fddLink id="fdd000143">JP2_FF</fddLink> .</p>
